The paper presents algorithms for approximate maximum flow in undirected graphs with good separator structures, which are common in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also makes use of spectral techniques, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
